====Provide a different thumbnail====
[[File:Anime stub 2.svg|thumb=Anime stub.png|alt=Example alt text|Example caption]]
You can link to one image from a thumbnail's small double-rectangle icon [[File:Magnify-clip.png|link=|alt=]], but display another image using "{{para|thumb|<var>Displayed image name</var>}}". This is intended for the rare cases when the Wikipedia software that reduces images to thumbnails does a poor job, and you want to provide your own thumbnail. In the example, the double-rectangle links to ''[[:File:Anime stub 2.svg]]'' but the image displayed is ''[[:File:Anime stub.png]]''.

<code><nowiki>[[File:Anime stub 2.svg|</nowiki>'''<span style="color:red;">thumb=''Anime stub.png''</span>'''<nowiki>|alt=Example alt text|Example caption]]</nowiki></code>

